      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNFILTERED (4) made his debut last start at a big quote but defied the market to grab second beaten 2 lengths over 1100m at this track. Should improve sharply and keeps the handy 3kg claim. ARIANNA'S GOLD (5) was beaten 1.75 lengths when resuming from a spell over 1200m at this track after leading them for home. Has a handy 2kg claim and is also a key runner. WINDARA WOLF (3) rates similarly off his 1.3L first-up defeat here over 1220m following a switch to the Gandy yard. He'd been off the scene for an age, and the former Victorian placed close up on a heavy track at Warrnambool last preparation. Is sure to have come on and has to be considered. MONCLERE (2) placed distantly last time but was good here prior over 1400m. Has been freshened and his best would see him in the finish.",
